This is their main distribution center, and they can answer all your FedEx questions. I had a package delivered to my home, addressed to someone I didn‚Äôt know. I went to a different FedEx and the package kept getting returned to my house. Then, I went here, and they were able to figure out the mystery behind the package, and made me feel better to return the package to its rightful owner.

For any purchases you must bring a government issued ID to complete the transaction. It‚Äôs a new rule in place, so just don‚Äôt leave your ID in the car or at home.

They have all the packing supplies you need to send off a package. Plenty of space out front for parking. The space is clean, if no one is there when you walk in, just wait and you‚Äôll be helped.<//text>

< Text>
This location only specializes in FedEx domestic and international shipments, hence the name, FedEx Ship Center.

Lines can get long if you drop by during lunch or close to the domestic and international shipment cut off times. Easy parking. I prefer this location to the FedEx Print and Ship Center on Maxella if I'm only doing shipping.

They've done away with the paper airway bills so the clerks have to enter names and addresses manually on the spot -- I don't have a FedEx account so I can't enter in the info via the website, but next time I go, I'm going to bring a typed list of address info so I don't have to dictate from/to infos regarding my shipments.<//Text>

<Review>Remember when you first tried Lambic and thought, wow, this stuff is amazing? Well, you can get sour ales‚Äîfor that is what Lambic is‚Äîclose by. Eric and the genius brewers behind their Casa Agria (Spanish for "house sour") in Oxnard have crafted a most amazing assortment of sour ales to delight and tantalize your palate (for the record, the ales I tried have not been sweet). Try the salty one (La Llorona)‚Äîdon't worry‚Äîit's only mildly salty. Or Mega Citronic‚Äîhoppy, citrusy, complex. Listening to Eric talk about his brews is like listening to a composer talk about his symphony: ‚ÄúWe collected the wild yeast in an organic field and then . . . we aged it for four months in a bourbon cask, then switched it to a port cask and finished it off with . . . " I don't remember the details, but I was spellbound listening‚Äîthese guys are off-the-chain serious about extreme creativity when it comes to brewmanship, changing and responding to what‚Äôs in season and imagineering exotic new tastes. But mostly, it's the ale. It's always about the ale. Just sip and think and enjoy. Casa Agria will be YUUGE someday, you can feel it. Now it's tiny, so go quickly and try‚Äîwhile you can still talk to Nick and company and get a dose of sour-mania first-hand.< /Review><pics>None<//pics><resp>None</resp>< gmapID>

< Review>
On october 20th, I got two pet guinea pigs. At first it was an obsession and I thought that it would never happen. My mother has pet chickens so we would go there for chicken food and various other chicken products. Seeing guinea pigs there every time crushed me knowing I would never be able to get them. When a circumstance arose that I could finally get guinea pigs, I freaked out. I thought I would have to go somewhere else to get actual guinea pig products and that they just had guinea pigs there, but they have the whole nine yards! Not to mention the fact that everybody there is super helpful  and sold us just the right products  to keep even the pickiest of pigs happy. Two months later I now have what I believe to be the happiest guinea pigs in the world thanks to Malibu feed bin and they're amazing selection a various pet products and pets themselves!</Review>

<UserId.>103127226838074847490< /UserId.>< Review>
This was my third rental through Sixt. The reason it was my third consecutive rental was that the prices are good and I never had a problem with them.  Until this third time. I had paid at least one month in advance and indicated I wanted a Mercedes class vehicle - or similar. I understand "or similar". The first time I rented, I also said I wanted a Mercedes (which they did not have when I went to pick up) and they instead gave me a Land Rover. THAT is "or similar".
When I picked this vehicle up it was not a Mercedes SUV - or similar. It was a Cadillac SUV.  I am NOT the only one who thinks a Cadillac is NOT in the same category as a Mercedes.  The attendant stated that "We rarely have a Mercedes available. We classify the Cadillac as in the same category as Mercedes". With nothing else available, according to the attendant, and my vacation ticking away,  I took the Cadillac.
The vehicle had not been cleaned. Specifically, the passenger seat had debris in the seams; there were white dusty marks on the glove box; the touch screen had fingerprints all over it (especially disturbing during Covid 19) and the exterior had black specs on it which the attendant said not to worry about, that this "had already been noted" as damage to the vehicle. These black specs subsequently washed off!!
When I returned the car, I told the very same attendant how dirty the vehicle was when I picked it up and my concern about it not having been properly cleaned which surely meant it had not been sanitized against the corona virus. The attendant told me that they sprayed the vehicles with a sanitizer; and then he assured me he would speak to whomever cleans vehicles upon return.
Oh, come on, Sixt!!  You just told me the procedure is to spray a vehicle with sanitizer BEFORE (or IN LIEU OF) cleaning it???
I would think that with business probably just beginning to pick up for you, that you would make certain every customer is a happy customer. The attendant should have offered me options when I stated that I was not pleased with the Cadillac SUV. AND YOU SHOULD HAVE MADE CERTAIN THE VEHICLE WAS PROPERLY SANITIZED.
No excuse for this.

I had made a reservation on 10/18 for a Toyota Yaris to be picked up at the Sixt agency in West Hollywood in Los Angeles. This car was reserved for 10/30 at 11 a.m. until 9/11 at 11 a.m.

It turns out that when I arrived at the agency to collect the car on 30/10, the car was not available and no other car at the same price was. I was asked to come back at 2 p.m. and that she would be available. So I came back at 2 p.m. and the car was still not available.

I can understand that some customers are late on the return of the car and I can accept to wait a few hours even if a commercial gesture would have been appreciable on your part. On the other hand, asking me to wait so long to find myself unable to honor my request is deplorable and indicates an appalling quality of service from a car rental agency.

Your agents on site took more than 30 minutes to find a solution to my problem. First I was offered a much more expensive car by offering me a reduction. Intrigued to be able to benefit from a Cadillac for less than a Toyota Yaris, I dig the subject with the agent and discover that in fact the reduction applies to a daily rate but that the total price will be double that that I have already paid for. I am starting to lose patience, I had reserved and paid for this car 12 days before, I still could not benefit from it 3 hours after the agreed schedule and I was offered an upgrade by disguising the fact that it would involve additional costs. It is simply outrageous.

Finally the agency offers me to pick up a car at the same price as mine in another agency, in Downtown LA and offers to go there with a rental van. It should be understood here that I am asked to do a job of exchanging cars between two Sixt agencies, therefore to do the work of the employees for them. And it's the only solution if I want to be able to recover a car at the price I paid. Another proof, if need be, of a dismal service.

What does it matter if I had an appointment elsewhere and that going to this agency distances me from several tens of kilometers from my appointment. What also matters to put in my hands a van whose volume is disproportionate compared to the city car that I had booked while experiencing, in addition, an incomparable urban traffic: that of Los Angeles.

I end up doing the car exchange at the Sixt agency in Downtown LA and leave with a Volkswagen Jetta at 3:45 pm. It was not the car I had reserved and we were 4:45 behind the time I was supposed to pick it up. The quality of service is catastrophic.

To flee !

<Review>Excellent service and quality!

The menu was clean and organized. Finally a menu with lots of nice pictures of foods. Excellent and so helpfulI. I wish other restaurant's menu could have more pictures.

The staff were kind and helpful.

As we entered in to the restaurant during lunch time, many visitors were there to eat.

We were quickly helped to sit down at a table and right away and another waitress came to receive our order.

We ordered several different dishes. The food were hot, fresh and tasted excellent!

The amount of salt in the food was ok but the amount of sugar in salads and other dishes were more than expected. We wish the sugar could be less and they could serve some sugar at side so the customer themself can decide how much sugar they want to add.

The waiting time from order to be served was ok.

The restroom:
We didn't see any restroom. Does this place have restroom?

<Review>What a wonderful place.  We stopped here after touring the Venice Canal houses.  We had the Krispy Ka Prao Chicken and the Roasted Duck Curry with a side of white, steamed rice.

First, the ambiance is just amazing. We sat outside, our table overlooking the canal, a fresh breeze lightly blowing in on a warm and sunny winter day.

The chicken was tender, falling off the bone, with a sticky, crispy skin and crispy basil. I probably could have eaten another entire serving.  The curry had a beautiful kick of spice to it and the duck was tasty.

The service was great too.  The server kept our water glasses full and checked in on us several times.

We would definitely return here again.<//Review></record></dataset><record>

This is what separates the elite business from average.

<Review>I went to Del Monte never playing here before. I have to say, it‚Äôs extremely expensive for what you get.. they should not be charging resort type rates for this club. Very old school traditional course, up and down, every hole is basically the same. I have played Pebbles other courses, Spyglass, Spanish Bay, and Pebble itself and all of those are amazing courses and well worth the extra money.. don‚Äôt waste your time at this place.

I also was told I would get a rental set that fits my playing style when I booked the reservation, (Men‚Äôs Left Hand, Stiff Shaft). My own clubs have X Stiff shafts. I get to the course and find out that they don‚Äôt even carry a Left Hand Stiff Shaft rental. Very disappointing... had to play with regular shafts. They did comp the rental, which was nice.. but the clubs just didn‚Äôt fit my playing style. I wish they had comped by round as well, because anyone that is an avid golfer can attest that it would just be a huge bummer to be used to hitting X Stiff shafts and then have to hit regulars, it was like hitting a childrens set.

I honestly would have left when I got there, had it not been that it was my grand fathers 85th birthday and I was treating him to a round. And he did enjoy it, so that is all that mattered to me at the end of the day. The guys we played with were fantastic as well.

The course just did not meet any of my expectations whatsoever, and the rental club situation was a cherry on top. I‚Äôll pay double/triple to play at Pebble‚Äôs other courses, any day.< /Review><Pictures>None</Pictures>< Response>

< Rating>
3<//Rating>
< Review>
Very much part of Californian golfing legend, Del Monte is a member of the impressive stable of courses owned and operated by Pebble Beach Resorts. Compared to its peers, which lie to the west on the ocean-facing shoreline of the Monterey Peninsula, Del Monte poses a less demanding and less scenic golfing challenge.
The final holes of this pleasant parkland course are played in front of the Hyatt Regency hotel, the 17th green located just a few feet away from the hotel terrace.< /Review>

(Translated by Google) Pebble Beach is the easiest golf course to round out of the four golf courses. It's different from Pebble Beach, Spyglass or Spanish Bays, and it's located on the inland mountain side, so it doesn't have any seaside views, but it's an open course that even beginners can round with well-maintained fairways and good course design.

(Translated by Google) Golf course in Pebble Beach. This is the easier of the four courses. Quite rustic. There is no pool, and the wind is small without the sea. There is a shop that serves breakfast, clothes, and golf equipment. There is no other beverage restaurant in the 18-hole court, but there are cars selling drinks and meals. There is no shower. It is inconvenient to wash the ball after hitting. But this is a general habit in American courts. It is relatively unaccustomed to Taiwanese golfers.

0x80d9523c3ba92779:0x1dd929f2dbdbec4e</Gmap_id>
< date>
1620111033344< /date>
<review>Yes, it's a bit odd having to rate a McDonald's, but tonight warranted me to actually leave a review. Normally, I'd just take a survey that is on the receipt-- but I didn't even get one. The girl at around 10:45 who was taking payments at the window was not having it.

I had decided last minute that I wanted to grab a coffee and she seemed absolutely disgruntled that I even had the audacity to order more. She even had a fan on (not even sure if that's allowed and keep in mind that it's a chilly night.

I get my food and she just gives it to me all without a single word. No semblance of basic customer service was given. I get it-- I've been there and done that but at least do the bare minimum and bid your customers goodbye or even a thank you.

The food was the usual from McD, but they made sure to practically fill my iced coffee to the brim with ice.

I usually don't really care too much in regards to fast food, but this experience in particular rubbed me the wrong way. Not getting a receipt and receiving customer support at this level is unacceptable for a business. If this is going to be the norm-- I'm afraid I'll take my business elsewhere to the jack in the box down the street. Hell, I'll even drive out of my way to the other mcdonalds on plaza blvd< /review><pics>None< /pics><resp>None< /resp>< Rating>
1<//Rating>

Nothing against the staff (they are always really helpful), but I have been going here now for about a month, and every time the soda machine is broken, but I am not told. The drinks are always flat or taste slightly off. If I was told on ordering at least I could order something else.

Fix your drinks machine please

Visited today after about a month, drinks machine was not working at all, so I had to have either tea or orange. I chose orange, then when I got to the register there was an extra charge of $2.50 for the OJ. If your machines are not working you shouldn't be charging your customers extra!
